The patient was a 35-year-old man with a history of chronic pain due to a spinal cord injury. He had been using medicinal cannabis for several years to manage his pain. His cannabis use consisted of smoking dried buds and the use of cannabis oil. The cannabis oil was obtained from a legal dispensary and was labeled as containing 70% THC and 1% CBD.

